      "decision": "Table partitioning + archival over unlimited growth",
      "gains": "Keeps index sizes manageable, query performance predictable, backup/restore times bounded.",
      "sacrifices": "Adds operational complexity. Queries spanning partitions need care. Accessing archived data requires a separate path.",
      "alternatives_considered": ["Bigger disk only (postpones problem 4-5 months)", "NoSQL migration (massive risk, unjustified at this scale)"]
